  "prompt": "Which are some kickass CV/ resume you have ever seen?",
  "response": "While I don't have direct access to specific resumes or CVs, I can highlight some features that are commonly found in outstanding resumes:\n\n1. **Visual Appeal**: A well-designed layout that is clean and easy to read can make a huge difference. Effective use of white space, headings, and bullet points helps in guiding the reader's eye.\n\n2. **Tailored Content**: Instead of a one-size-fits-all resume, exceptional CVs are tailored to the specific job description, highlighting relevant experience and skills that directly align with the position.\n\n3. **Strong Summary/Profile Section**: A powerful opening statement that encapsulates the candidate\u2019s key achievements, skills, and career objectives can make a great first impression.\n\n4. **Quantifiable Achievements**: The best resumes quantify achievements with numbers and specific examples (e.g., \"Increased sales by 20% over six months\").\n\n5. **Keywords Optimization**: Incorporating industry-specific keywords and phrases helps in getting past ATS (Applicant Tracking Systems) and ensures the resume reaches human eyes.\n\n6. **Clear Branding**: A unique personal brand, sometimes highlighted with a personal logo or specific color scheme, can make a resume stand out.\n\n7. **Professional Experience**: A strong emphasis on relevant experience with a focus on achievements over duties is crucial. The STAR (Situation, Task, Action, Result) method can help in clearly articulating experiences.\n\n8. **Skills Section**: A detailed skills section that highlights both hard and soft skills, often categorized for better clarity.\n\n9. **Education and Certifications**: Relevant educational background and any certifications that add value to the candidate's professional profile.\n\n10. **Online Integration**: Including links to professional networks, portfolios, or personal websites can provide more depth to a candidate's profile.\n\n11. **Error-Free and Consistent**: Attention to detail with no spelling or grammatical errors and consistent formatting throughout.\n\nThese elements, when combined, create a powerful and impactful resume that effectively communicates a candidate's value and potential to employers.",
